https://github.com/sibiraj-s/ngx-editor/:
For anyone encountering this issue, here's a workaround that bypasses `setContent()` by creating a fresh EditorState directly in a component that wraps NgxEditor:

```ts
  import { EditorState } from 'prosemirror-state';

  writeValue(content: string) {
      const doc = schema.nodeFromJSON(toDoc(content));  // or parse your content however needed

      // Create a new state with the same plugins but a fresh document.
      // This sets the content without recording it in the undo history.
      const newState = EditorState.create({
          doc,
          plugins: this.editor.view.state.plugins,
      });
      this.editor.view.updateState(newState);
  }
```

This creates a new editor state with the document content but a fresh history, so pressing Ctrl/Cmd+Z won't undo the initial content load.

Note: This resets the entire undo history, so any previous edits will no longer be undoable. For our use case (ControlValueAccessor writeValue), this is acceptable since we only use it for initial load and programmatic resets.

