https://github.com/dg/dibi/issues/433:
Hi!

I'd like to revive this issue (using Dibi 5.0.2, PHP 8.4).

There is a native SQLSRV function in PHP [`sqlsrv_num_rows`](https://www.php.net/manual/en/function.sqlsrv-num-rows.php), which allows retrieving the row count for result sets **if** the query is executed with the `Scrollable` flag.  
Currently, Dibi doesn't expose this functionality for the SQLSRV driver.

## Suggested implementation

**In `SqlsrvResult.php`:**

```php
public function getRowCount(): int
{
    if ($this->scrollable) {
        $rows = sqlsrv_num_rows($this->resultSet);
        return $rows === false ? 0 : $rows;
    }
    throw new Dibi\NotSupportedException('Row count is not available for unbuffered queries.');
}
```

This, however, requires that the query itself is executed with the `Scrollable` option.

---

**In the driver, `query()` method needs to allow passing this option:**

```php
public function query(string $sql, array $params = [], array $options = []): ?Dibi\ResultDriver 
{
    $this->affectedRows = null;
    $res = sqlsrv_query($this->connection, $sql, $params, $options); 

    if ($res === false) {
        $info = sqlsrv_errors();
        throw new Dibi\DriverException($info[0]['message'], $info[0]['code'], $sql);

    } elseif (is_resource($res)) {
        $this->affectedRows = Helpers::false2Null(sqlsrv_rows_affected($res));
        return sqlsrv_num_fields($res)
            ? $this->createResultDriver($res)
            : null;
    }

    return null;
}
```

Alternatively, consider splitting the query into `doQuery` and `query` for easier overriding/extensibility.

```php
protected function doQuery(string $sql): false|resource 
{
    return sqlsrv_query($this->connection, $sql); 
}

public function query(string $sql): ?Dibi\ResultDriver 
{
    $this->affectedRows = null;
    $res = doQuery($sql); 

    if ($res === false) {
        $info = sqlsrv_errors();
        throw new Dibi\DriverException($info[0]['message'], $info[0]['code'], $sql);

    } elseif (is_resource($res)) {
        $this->affectedRows = Helpers::false2Null(sqlsrv_rows_affected($res));
        return sqlsrv_num_fields($res)
            ? $this->createResultDriver($res)
            : null;
    }

    return null;
}
```

---

**Note:**  
The `'Scrollable' => SQLSRV_CURSOR_KEYSET` option only works for **SELECT** queries.  
If you run e.g. `INSERT`, `UPDATE`, or any other statement with this option, it will fail.  
That’s why this should **not** be set as a default for all queries.

A typical pattern (to allow projects to easily set this only for SELECTs) could look like this:

```php
public function doQuery(string $sql): ?Dibi\ResultDriver
{
    if (str_starts_with(strtoupper(trim($sql)), 'SELECT')) {
        $options['Scrollable'] = SQLSRV_CURSOR_KEYSET;
    }
    return sqlsrv_query($this->connection, $sql, [], $options ?? []);
}
```

This way, large projects can globally override the logic as needed, and avoid errors for non-SELECT queries.

---

## Why

- `rowCount()` is a common requirement for paginated results, UI tables, etc.
- The change is backwards compatible: if `'Scrollable'` is not set, it will throw an exception as before.
- This implementation does **not** affect any other functionality or SQL statements – everything else behaves as before, all values returned stay unchanged.
- It enables projects to extend row counting functionality for SELECTs **without** needing to implement a custom driver. Developers can either override query (in case of `doQuery()`) behavior globally, or set options individually at specific places in the code, so there is no need for any large-scale override.
- Only when used properly (i.e., with SELECT and the right flag) will `getRowCount` work as expected; otherwise, it safely throws same as now.

> Given that, this should be safe for a minor (semver) release, as it doesn't break anything for existing projects and just enables additional use cases for those who need it.

---

**Thanks for considering!**  
